Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.08,0:05:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(962.667,649)}Ten: Tenho-doori no Kaidanji\N(Nice guy on the path of Tenho)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.08,0:05:14.38,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(973.333,907.667)}Episode 5
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.65,0:05:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What round it it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.25,0:05:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,South round 4, last hand
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.55,0:05:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy from Tokyo is in 3rd
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.25,0:05:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,3rd place?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.35,0:05:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But his last hand is good
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.95,0:05:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the sort of hand that could pull off a sudden reversal if it gets big
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.00,0:05:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.45,0:06:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Honiitsu, ShoSan with one dora. A Baiman hand that will put him on top.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.65,0:06:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's bold he can discard a 3/6/9 for a single wait on Red Dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.65,0:06:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Later he could draw a Red dragon for a 3rd turn as dealer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.80,0:06:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But this guy's going for chitoitsu. A previously undiscarded tile like Red Dragon could be dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.25,0:06:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.85,0:06:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,6,400 points
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.15,0:06:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, darn
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.28,0:06:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,so waiting on Red Dragon, hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.30,0:06:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-you two KNOW each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.40,0:06:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a little
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.51,0:06:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.51,0:07:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,o-okay
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.31,0:07:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.31,0:07:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Today you lost on purpose, didn't you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.60,0:07:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's clear...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.90,0:07:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that's was no reason for you to discard the Red Dragon there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.68,0:07:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course. Leave it to you to..
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.81,0:07:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to show them my hand
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.70,0:07:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,my skill, yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.70,0:07:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but also my luck
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.65,0:07:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to show them... my game flow
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.50,0:07:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So THAT'S the number one guy on the East team?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.95,0:07:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This'll be a blowout for the West team won't it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.65,0:07:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one second
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.58,0:07:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn over Ten's subsequent draws from the point he lost
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.40,0:07:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,y-yessir
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.60,0:08:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A Red Dragon, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.10,0:08:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,yes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.85,0:08:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but, how?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.45,0:08:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You lot couldn't possibly understand, but
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.30,0:08:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that guy could SENSE there was a Red Dragon coming
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.95,0:08:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You thought the Eastern head was pure trash,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.71,0:08:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it don't look like that at all
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.10,0:08:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're late
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.20,0:08:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The 3rd member of the East team
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.00,0:08:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(918.667,122.333)}Asai "Ganpai" Ginji
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.78,0:08:56.68,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(584,841)}Ganpai: (lit. "wounded tile") is the cheat of marking tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.75,0:08:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(964,109)}A most valued artisan
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.08,0:08:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(958.667,197)}through which almost no opponent can see
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.40,0:09:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a master of the tiles with the skill near that of a contortionist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.70,0:09:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happened? We still need one man for the East team?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.95,0:09:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no good
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.75,0:09:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A notable ringer took the cash and simply vanished
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.65,0:09:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,burns me the fuck up
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.65,0:09:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Without doubt this contest is gonna be tough to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.50,0:09:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And Akagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.50,0:09:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked, but couldn't get him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.50,0:09:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I see
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.45,0:09:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Breh
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.45,0:09:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How about {\i1\b1}him{\i0\b0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.91,0:09:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,no
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.25,0:09:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He's no good for the East team
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.25,0:09:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.35,0:09:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you to wash your hands of this world
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.38,0:09:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This battle
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.38,0:09:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is no place for a normie like you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.75,0:09:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But at least he's got the game
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.70,0:09:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and some spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.61,0:10:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,just try me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.61,0:10:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,for as far as you can use me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.95,0:10:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,For two long years I've been restless
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.20,0:10:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting for this moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.00,0:10:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and so
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.10,0:10:11.30,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,NO
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.30,0:10:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight your battles in the normie world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.30,0:10:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It... suits you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.80,0:10:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Kid, how old are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.00,0:10:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,27
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.95,0:10:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Rash, brash,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.95,0:10:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,reckless
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.95,0:10:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a good look bout him, doesn't he.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.95,0:10:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks just like you did, Ten. Long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.10,0:10:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Our opponents won't be expecting a greenhorn like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.78,0:10:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He might just be our... trump card.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.15,0:11:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Please
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.05,0:12:41.00,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1332,679.667)}通天閣\NTsū-TEN-kaku
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.15,0:13:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The West team roster
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.45,0:13:14.05,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1420,1053)}Harada Katsumi\NMitsui Jyuuji\NAkutsu\N{\b1}Soga Mitsui{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.45,0:13:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.75,0:13:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.75,0:13:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Soga's name is here
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.41,0:13:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Those West bastards
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.25,0:13:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They even pulled Soga into this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.70,0:13:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Soga?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.85,0:13:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.65,0:13:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A master who controlled the underworld for years
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.48,0:13:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Over a ten year period he didn't lose once
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.98,0:13:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But I heard he retied because of poor health.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.60,0:13:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My god. To think even Soga is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.01,0:14:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,First, there is a proposal from the West team.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.00,0:14:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.00,0:14:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It is suggested both teams
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.00,0:14:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,should propose a single
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.00,0:14:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,additional Mahjong rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.60,0:14:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as you prefer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.21,0:14:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.70,0:14:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The East team players
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.31,0:14:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.25,0:14:43.35,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1000,353)}Ten Takashi\NAsai Ginji\NIsokaze　Ken\NIgawa Hiroyuki
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.58,0:14:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The East team looks useless
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.10,0:14:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten's the only smart one
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.58,0:14:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't look like the East team could get Akagi
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.95,0:14:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though we went to great pains to get Soga,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.10,0:15:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it's looking like it's going to be a dull match.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.70,0:15:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,ha ha ha
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.70,0:15:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be time momentarily.\NPlease proceed to the contest area.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.70,0:15:11.65,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(373.333,422.333)}Fukumoto Sensei-->
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.25,0:15:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.35,0:15:32.65,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(957.334,883.667)}#/tv/shows posse assembles
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.50,0:15:32.65,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm thinking they're back
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.60,0:15:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a time restriction rule
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.85,0:15:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone caught cheating hands over his point box.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.75,0:15:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Among the 8 people here
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.75,0:15:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,only four will advance to the final round
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.78,0:15:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And our proposed additional rule
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.25,0:15:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Mangan-Shibari
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.25,0:16:00.85,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(972,205)}Mangan-Shibari (満貫縛り): A rule restricting winning hands to Mangan or higher. No "trivial" wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.25,0:15:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Wins less than Mangan are just useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.70,0:16:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And there is no penalty for not achieving Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.65,0:16:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.20,0:16:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.68,0:16:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,How about a rule eliminating accumulated wins
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.70,0:16:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.51,0:16:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally points go to the winner
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.60,0:16:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but now, the points of someone who wins a hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.60,0:16:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,would absolutely never increase.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.35,0:16:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This rule
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.05,0:16:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,ensures a single hit point reversal is always possible
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.95,0:16:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If points don't increase someone with no points can't recover
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.65,0:16:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you deal into someone's hand, it instantly starts a countdown to death
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.90,0:16:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,HA HA HA
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.90,0:16:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,TOP LAFF
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.85,0:16:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we accept
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.95,0:17:25.58,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(980,893)}East Round 1
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.80,0:18:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.70,0:18:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,H-hayai\NOn only the 3rd turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.90,0:18:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,even with a Mangan-shibari?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.18,0:18:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a risky discard
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.45,0:18:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, seeing Harada's discards, it makes me suspicious of Sou (bamboo) tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.65,0:19:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore I guess other tiles are okay, but I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.01,0:19:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This Riichi is meant to measure the skill of these two.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.35,0:19:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Or to put it another way, to find which is an easy mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.18,0:19:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking at the bias in his discards
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.90,0:19:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone would have a bad feeling about Sou tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.65,0:19:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken went with his gut feeling, so he's the type that acts on hunches
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.65,0:19:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,HOWEVER
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.40,0:19:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroyuki is the type that places logic as a priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.75,0:19:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll follow theory in this situation
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.05,0:19:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and he'll certainly play the appropriate safe tile, BUT
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.10,0:19:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that normal style of playing is the worst here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.15,0:20:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on Mitsui's discards, this ought to be the 4th and last 2Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.05,0:20:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,this OUGHT to pass here
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.65,0:20:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.78,0:20:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one Ura-dora of two
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.71,0:20:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.71,0:20:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lucky
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.70,0:20:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.95,0:20:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to fall for a hackneyed trap like this
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.60,0:20:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we should talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.81,0:22:25.40,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(952,885)}East Round 3
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.00,0:22:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.65,0:22:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,s-sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.15,0:22:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,H-he's missing a tile!\NHe's only got 12!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.25,0:22:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in Shohai. What an incompetent mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.25,0:22:57.85,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(948,113)}Shohai(少牌): Having too few tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.75,0:24:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,'zat a one Pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.71,0:24:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,RON
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.85,0:24:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,SuuAnKou (4 concealed triplets)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.85,0:24:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He's no longer in Shohai!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.01,0:24:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,H-he's done the UNTHINKABLE
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.55,0:24:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Among the rules of Mahjong, that one known as Shohai is a peculiarly odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.00,0:24:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,While it's clearly a foul, you can't stop the game for it. Only disregard a win.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.71,0:24:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's my advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.71,0:24:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When I'm in Shohai, no one pays me any attention
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.70,0:24:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought I could take down Harada with a clean game
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.10,0:25:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All that's needed is for him to see I have the full 13 tiles when I reveal my hand
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.50,0:25:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The wall before me has an East wind on the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.10,0:25:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Only I saw it when I knocked it over before
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.95,0:25:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so, putting the east wind and 6 Sou from the wall in my hand
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.35,0:25:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I can pull the 1Pin Harada discarded on the first turn
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.85,0:25:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,take the 1Pin and switch it out
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.90,0:25:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can pull an East wind and 1Pin into my hand
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.80,0:25:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Completing my SuuAnKou single tile wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.35,0:25:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All that remains to to RON THE FUCK out of Harada on his 1Pin
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.40,0:25:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,SuuAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.70,0:25:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,47,000 points
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.55,0:25:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The contest is over
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.55,0:25:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,H-harada dealt into a dealer Yakuman!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.15,0:25:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,hey now
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.15,0:25:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,don't take us for fools
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.00,0:25:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That wall in front of you went from 9 tiles to 8 tiles wide
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.00,0:26:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obvious you pulled two tiles from that wall
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.20,0:26:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the hell you on about m8?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.20,0:26:05.20,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,YOU FUCKER!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.85,0:26:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Mitsui
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.20,0:26:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,just be quiet a moment
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.60,0:26:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,BUT
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.25,0:26:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If anyone is going to fight over this, it's me
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.40,0:26:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll SETTLE IT
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.85,0:26:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're called "Ken" aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.35,0:26:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be sure to remember that name
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.00,0:26:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken clearly pulled two tiles from his wall
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.70,0:26:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(992,109)}And he's still got ONE IN HIS HAND
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.75,0:26:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(976,101)}What's he going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.40,0:26:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(968,117)}Cut away mane
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.71,0:26:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(964,121)}but if there's no tile in that hand
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.75,0:26:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,93)}with one cut you only confirm
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.05,0:26:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,121)}YOU LOSE
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.45,0:27:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(968,109)}Do you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.01,0:27:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(952,121)}When someone dies from a gunshot wound
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.45,0:27:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(984,117)}they die senseless, in shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.45,0:27:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(956,117)}HOWEVER
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.45,0:27:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(944,137)}death by stabbing is a LOT more painful
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.38,0:27:15.38,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(948,217)}w-what are you saying？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.41,0:27:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(964,117)}This Mahjong is a scramble over life and death!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.45,0:27:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(980,133)}If I confirm my opponent is cheating I take his life!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.95,0:27:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(964,117)}and I'll do so at my leisure
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.95,0:27:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(936,117)}AT AN AUTOPSY
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.95,0:27:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(952,105)}S-STOP PLEASE
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.90,0:27:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(968,121)}too late
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.95,0:27:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1008,129)}HA HA HA HA
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.75,0:27:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This man kills without qualm
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.95,0:27:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.81,0:27:55.81,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd mix it up a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.51,0:27:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us confirm your two players
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.08,0:27:58.08,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,My short sword will taste blood
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.25,0:28:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroyuki is cornered\NIt's over
